issue.title: Inference Session in GPT-NEO-1.3B fails

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Inference Session in GPT-NEO-1.3B fails**

I exported the model GPT-NEO-1.3B to onnx with this command:

`python -m transformers.onnx --model=EleutherAI/gpt-neo-1.3B --feature=causal-lm onnx/`

I get a lot the files in the onnx folder plus the model.onnx. I tested the model with this code:

```
import onnx
# Check we can load the model
onnx_model = onnx.load('onnx/model.onnx')
# Check the model
onnx.checker.check_model('onnx/model.onnx', full_check=True)
#print(onnx.helper.printable_graph(onnx_model.graph))
print("Ok")
```
The result is OK.

However, when I try to do the inference with this code:

```
import onnxruntime as ort
from transformers import GPT2Tokenizer, GPTNeoModel
import torch

tokenizer = GPT2Tokenizer.from_pretrained("EleutherAI/gpt-neo-1.3B")
utterance = "I want to order a Pizza"
tokens_ids = tokenizer(utterance, return_tensors="pt")

input_ids = torch.cat((tokens_ids['input_ids'], torch.zeros(1, 120, dtype=torch.int64)), dim=1)
attention_mask = torch.cat((tokens_ids['attention_mask'], torch.zeros(1, 120, dtype=torch.int64)), dim=1)
decoder_input_ids = torch.zeros(1, 128, dtype=torch.int64)
decoder_attention_mask = torch.zeros(1, 128, dtype=torch.int64)

print(input_ids)
print(attention_mask)

options = ort.SessionOptions()
print(options)

ort_session = ort.InferenceSession('C:/Users/Jorge/PycharmProjects/inteBERT/onnx/model.onnx', options)

print("Ok")
```
I get the error:

**[ONNXRuntimeError] : 1 : FAIL : Deserialize tensor transformer.h.16.attn.attention.out_proj.bias failed.open file transformer.h.16.attn.attention.out_proj.bias fail, errcode = 2 - The system cannot find the specified file.**

Nevertheless, the file transformer.h.16.attn.attention.out_proj.bias is in the onnx folder.

The error occurs in the line: 

`ort_session = ort.InferenceSession('C:/Users/Jorge/PycharmProjects/inteBERT/onnx/model.onnx', options)`

Please, can you someone give me an advice?

issue.title: Fix load failure for onnx model with external data and slash (/) in path [Windows]

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 

GetDirNameFromFilePath currently assumes path using backslash. If user gives a ONNX model with external data, and path uses slash (/) instead of backslash (\\), ORT cannot extract the directory from path to locate external data file.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.

Related issues: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/5418, #11708
